 procedure to the 3D Stokes problem by\nproviding a direct proof of the required coerciveness property, that is without\nargueing by contradiction, and by using the natural norm of each space instead\nof mesh-dependent norms. Finally, we briefly describe concrete examples of\ndiscrete spaces satisfying the aforementioned hypotheses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Jun 2014 12:50:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-06-10"}
